Bio: 

Joshua M. Fulton (Cutt Throat) born May 6, 1987 in Baltimore, Maryland and grew up in South Baltimore on Heath and Clarkson. Cutt Throat was raised by his mother and father, with 2 brothers, a half brother, and a half sister. His parents separated while he was in gradeschool. His father moved to Fargo, ND while Cutt Throat stayed in Baltimore with his mother. Cutt Throat dropped out of high school due to lack of attendance and began running the streets. He was exposed to a urban lifestyle where he discovered he had a gift - cypher rapping on street corners around the neighborhood - and attracted attention from locals with the help of his family ties all throughout South Baltimore. He quickly earned the respect and love from various fans in many Baltimore neighborhoods with a rythmatic flo, realistic story lines, and remarkable wordplay about his life experiences.   So he decided to purchase his own studio equipment so he could start engineering himself and other MC's in Baltimore. After learning to engineer he moved back with his father and oldest brother to Fargo. His brother was also a rapper by the stagname Furious having success and opening up for signed artist's in Fargo. They started a group called "Dem Krack Boyz" under Quad City Fam with a MC named Infrared G from Chicago, Dat Boy Blitz from Red Lake, Minnesota, Drew Burner from Marietta, Georgia and  Furious and Cutt Throat formerly known as Dickhead from Baltimore, Maryland. Making the four cities combined for Quad City Fam where they made various mixtapes and songs together. Then Cutt Throat returned to Baltimore missing the city life, his mother, and other siblings. Upon returning he moved to Morrell Park in South Baltimore and was incarcerated for several crimes he did not commit and realized he needed to get out of the streets before he no longer had that opportunity. Upon his release he recorded another mixtape called "That Dickhead & Nitty shit" self-titled  with a neighborhood MC named Lil Nitty. Nitty eventually introduced Cutt Throat to Ryan Escolopio the CEO of iBOT Records and began recording his music in a high grade professional studio releasing his solo mixtape  "2 Real for the Radio". After being introduced to Sayne, Cutt Throat was introduced to Test Me at Powerhitter Records by Sayne. Shortly after, Cutt Throat introduced Sayne to his engineer  Ryan Esclopioa the CEO of iBOT Records. After Cutt Throat & Sayne recorded about 2 songs together at iBOT Records they developed a healthy competition for one another writing songs and recording tracks. Cutt Throat & Sayne decided to start a partnership on "Yellow Tape Ent." and began working on their debut album together called "Undeniable" which later broke records at Rams Head Live for most sold tickets at an underground event. 

Currently: This summer of 2013 Josh AKA Cutt Throat was diagnosed with Testicular cancer, this was devastating news for him and his whole family, but did not hold him back from working on his music. As the cancer news wasn't bad enough Josh had to have several emergency surgeries back to back for life threatening blood clots. Josh learned that he would have to complete four rounds of chemo therapy, after they were complete scans showed that he would have to have more chemo at a higher dose. This treatment literally almost killed him as his body could not handle much more. During this time Josh STILL worked on furthering his career as a solo artist, he has done two mix tapes, several shows in the Baltimore and surrounding areas, and dropped several new videos all while undergoing his extreme chemo therapy. As this has been one of the toughest journeys in Josh's AKA Cutt Throats life, his music is what gives him the drive to keep him fighting this fight.

Stefano Lucarelli better known as Steve Dub is an Italian dj/producer active since 1981. His wide musical culture, ranging from jazz to soul, funk, hip hop, reggae and R&B, has made him one of urban culture‚Äôs pioneers in Italy. Over the past 20 years, his music selections have not only given birth to some of the coolest Milano‚Äôs Nights but strongly contributed to increase the hype around clubs like Plastic, Soul To Soul, Atm Bar, Le Bataclan, The Black and Biko, and, in addition, have been chosen as soundtrack for Prada, Lawrence Steele and Katharine Hamnet‚Äôs fashion shows. Official Italian dj for Vibe magazine, during his career Steve has played and produced lives and animated parties for the likes of Quincy Jones, Mary J. Blige, Spike Lee, Busta Rhymes, Wyclef Jean, Gang Starr, Naughty by Nature, Paris, Mariah Carey, Lenny Kravitz, Bilal, Pharoae Monch, Slum Village, Coultrain, Myron & E and Jordan Rakei. He has also decisively helped to build the success of some of the most popular hip hop radio shows in Italy, such as One-Two One-Two and Soulsista on Radio Deejay, Milangeles on Radio Capital, Hands Up on Station One and Urban Suite on Rai Radio 2. As a composer and producer he has worked with the leading names of the Italian‚Äôs hip hop and R&B scene, including Irene Lamedica, Chief & Soci, Le Sacre Scuole, DJ Skizo and Golden Bass. Among its productions there are some tracks for the legendary label Acid Jazz. He‚Äôs currently one of the resident djs of Biko Club and collaborates with Soulfood Promotion for the organization of events and live concerts. He‚Äôs the CEO of Too Deep Records and one of the founder and main contributors of akaSoulsista.com.

FOLLOW ME ON FACEBOOK Serge Nikitin (mostly known as Nikitin) is the Russian music producer/DJ who started to shape the sound more than 15 years ago. Got fame in hip-hop scene with the album ‚Äú24 rhythms‚Äù, which was produced in early 2000, and currently considered as the classics of the Russian hip- hop music. In the mid 2000 he was a part of techno duo Nikitin & Semikashev, who got released on Global Underground, Noir Music, Great stuff, Kling Klong, Robotronic, Toolroom and many other labels. Their music was supported and often played and charted by Steve Lawler, Miss Kittin, Ivan Smagghe, Noir and other DJs. In the end of first decade of 2000 he became a resident of 2 legendary Moscow venues "Gorod" and then "Arma 17" (which has cemented reputation as the Russia's finest clubs) and started active artist gigs around the world's clubs and festivals like legendary "Love Parade" in Germany or KaZantip in Crimea. Since 2010, Nikitin is a resident of Kolombo‚Äôs famous LouLou Records imprint, where special handcrafted groove is the king, also recently released on Highway, Neim, Dear Deer, Toolroom and others.

Leyder was raised and born on the "island of music", Cuba. His artistic journey began at the age of 11 when he entered the Art School of Santiago de Cuba. His education revolved around painting, dance and, of course, music. During his studies, Leyder realized that his love for music was more than a casual one and decided to dedicate himself to the art. Gifted with a strong and melodious voice he focussed on singing. 

He has practiced his craft as a singer in local theatre productions and International Festivals, and has been featured  as a vocal soloist in local clubs. He also belonged to a professional theatre group that travelled throughout Cuba.

Leyder's  professional career extended into the realm of popular media. He became something of a television personality while hosting a local program in Santiago de Cuba. He also became a radio program host of a municipal radio station. All the while, gaining more experience as a presenter and entertainer in live shows as well as at carnivals and other diverse cultural events that showcased his talents. He has established himself as both a serious artist and a crowd pleaser.

In  2002 after landing a contract as headliner  his reputation was solidified throughout the region as he performed regularly at various Hotels in Varadero . Since his arrival in Montreal in March 2007, Leyder has been busy acclimatizing himself to his new surroundings and learning Canada's two official languages, English and French. Pilch is a successful producer/remixer from Devon, England and has been writing dance music for over 30 years!!.  It all started back in the day when he was using his 'Techno Sound' sampler and using OctaMed on his Amiga 500 writing 4 track bangers!

He's released & remixed tracks on quite a few labels and has been remixed by Ali Payami, Longrange (ex Orbital man Phil Hartnoll), Kid Massive as well as Barry Ashworth (Dogtown Clash) to name a few reputable artists.

Pilch has featured on several compilations and has also released under the guise of 'The Officials' as well as a few cheeky bootlegs as 'Pilch + Play'.

These days you'll find him creating once again using Ableton 10 as his DAW of choice. His drive and inspiration is formed from listening to countless hours of melodic house and anything on the AnjunaDeep label.

Pilch's latest music has found homes on the AzariRecords and BBOP music labels and there's plenty more to come.
